  "prompt": "Was Khizr Khan paid over 100k by CNN and NBC and 175k by the DNC?",
  "response": "There were claims circulating that Khizr Khan, the Gold Star father who gave a speech at the Democratic National Convention in 2016, was paid large sums of money by CNN, NBC, and the DNC. However, these claims were debunked, and there is no credible evidence to support them.\n\nFact-checking organizations such as Snopes have investigated these allegations and found them to be baseless. Khan's speech at the DNC was widely seen as a personal and heartfelt testimony about the loss of his son, Humayun Khan, who was killed in Iraq. It was part of his support for Hillary Clinton's presidential campaign, and no substantial evidence has been presented to prove that he was paid these amounts by CNN, NBC, or the DNC.\n\nIn situations like this, it is important to rely on verified information from reputable sources.",
